reviews.review_text: dayonthegreen I was only 11 in 1974, but I did like the GD, wished I coulda seen a wall of sound show.  I would love to hear NRPS & Commander Cody sets from this gig!

I love this Matrix I like Matrix in general...but you get a good sense of the distance and volume in this concert.  You can feel you are outside.  You can feel how Phil fills out the sound with the low notes.  

Plus...man o Man this Playin' is smokin!  Especially the first segment.

Around 14:30 Phil starts playing after a couple minute break and it just goes into a fantastic Tiger.  But they don't stop afterwards!  They keep the frantic pace up until they just bubble into Wharf Rat.

You get Tigered into a black hole, and spit out into rotational chaos that doesn't stop.  Mind blowing!!!
